<seg id="1045">& Povray; supports two methods of super-sampling. as a standard is an adaptive, non-recursive method; adaptively because the super-sampling is the neighbouring pixels with inputs. the second method is adaptive-recursive; recursive because every pixel is distributed again and again because the recursion depth depends on the calculated color values.</seg>
<seg id="1046">If you choose the first method, POV-Ray follows a beam per pixel. if the difference between the color values to the adjacent pixels is exceeded, then both pixels are processed by tracking a certain additional number of pixels with super-sampling. if you set the depth value to 4, a grid of 4x4 additional points will be calculated, at a depth value of 5 then 5x5 (25) additional beams per pixel.</seg>
